This paper involves constructing an astronomical catalog using Bayesian variational inference and parallel computing on a supercomputer. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the use of Bayesian inference and machine learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves image processing and analysis, which could place it in the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of high-performance computing and optimization techniques could also make it relevant to the Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-category.
